<section id="home-work-lab" class="autofit-grid wrapper">
	<h2 class="section-title" id="home-work-title">
		work I do for clients; and lab:
	</h2>
	<div class="card stack">
		<CloudinaryVideo publicId="lifesci-project" controls width="100%" />
		<div class="project-description stack">
			<p>
				I built the website for
				<a href="https://lifescicommunications.com" class="link">
					LifeSci Communications</a
				>. It has a complex, modern layout, and every page has different line
				animations on scroll.
				<a href="/project/lifesci-project-details/" class="link"
					>Project details.</a
				>
			</p>
			<p class="tech">
				<span> Tech:</span>
				WordPress, Elementor, Greensock
			</p>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="card stack">
		<CloudinaryVideo publicId="ED" controls width="100%" />
		<div class="project-description stack">
			<p>
				At <a href="https://www.equivalent.design" class="link"
					>Equivalent Design</a
				>, I’m responsible for creating all the accessible SVG animations. I
				clean the SVGs, make them performant & WCAG compliant. e.g., in the
				animation for Sam, the guide dog above, I added support for
				<strong>
					reduced motion, light & dark mode, high contrast mode, reader app,
					etc.
				</strong>
			</p>
			<p class="tech">
				<span> Tech:</span>
				SVG, Greensock
			</p>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="card stack">
		<CloudinaryVideo publicId="scrolling-demos" controls width="100%" />
		<div class="project-description stack">
			<p>
				The client wanted to have 2 demos created using 4 panels and a pop up.
				This they would integrate it in their app on their own. In the first
				demo, 4 panels scrolls horizontally from left to right. In the second
				demo, 4 panels scrolls vertically from bottom to top. Both the demos
				panels are scrollable using anchors as well.
			</p>
			<p class="tech">
				<span> Tech:</span>
				Greensock, ScrollTrigger
			</p>
		</div>
	</div>
